title: Microsoft Defender for Office 365 Low Severity AIR Alert Handled Automatically
rule:
{'uuid': '6fab6947-5cec-4241-97b3-8f4aba02ecf7', 'name': 'Microsoft Defender for Office 365 Low Severity AIR Alert Handled Automatically', 'description': 'Microsoft Defender for Office 365 includes the capability to run Automated investigation and response (AIR) actions. This rule detects when a Low or Informational severity alert triggered an automated investigation, and remediation was conducted automatically. Low and Informational alerts include when an email is reported by a user, or when a malicious email is removed after delivery.', 'severity': 30, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  selection:
    service.name: AirInvestigation
    office365.investigation.alert.severity:
    - Low
    - Informational
    office365.investigation.status:
    - No threats found
    - Remediated
  condition: selection'}

    event.category: threat
  condition: selection'}

title: Suspicious Cmd.exe Command Line
rule:
{'uuid': '367530ca-3ad5-4bf7-a71c-cfce5f1e7905', 'name': 'Suspicious Cmd.exe Command Line', 'description': 'Detection on suspicious cmd.exe command line seen being used by some attackers (e.g. Lazarus with Word macros). This requires Windows process command line logging.', 'severity': 80, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': "detection:
  selection1:
    process.command_line|contains|all:
    - cmd
    - /c
    - copy
    - /b
    process.parent.name: '*'
  selection2:
    process.command_line|contains|all:
    - cmd
    - /c
    - start
    - /b
    process.parent.name: '*'
  filter:
  - process.parent.name:
    - pycharm.exe
    - pycharm64.exe
    - idea64.exe
    - code.exe
    - atlassian companion.exe
    - webstorm64.exe
  - process.command_line|contains: headdynam.pl
  condition: 1 of selection* and not filter"}

title: Opening Of a Password File
rule:
{'uuid': '1c6bd311-8f05-4188-bdbf-42d95b66536d', 'name': 'Opening Of a Password File', 'description': 'Command line detection of common office software opening some password related file. It could be a security breach if an unauthorized user access it.', 'severity': 30, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  file_name:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - mdp
    - password
    - mot de passe
    - mots de passe
  process:
    process.name:
    - notepad.exe
    - winword.exe
    - excel.exe
    - powerpnt.exe
    - outlook.exe
  filter1:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - firefox.exe
    - msedge.exe
    - chrome.exe
    - Office16
  filter2:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - reset
    - forgot
    - "R\xE9initialiser"
  condition: file_name and process and not (filter1 and filter2)'}

title: Remote Monitoring and Management Software - AnyDesk
rule:
{'uuid': '7ad01b57-2538-4486-ae6e-5630a172137d', 'name': 'Remote Monitoring and Management Software - AnyDesk', 'description': 'Detect artifacts related to the installation or execution of the Remote Monitoring and Management tool AnyDesk.', 'severity': 75, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  selection:
  - process.name:
    - AnyDesk.exe
    - anydesk
  - process.executable|endswith:
    - \AnyDesk.exe
    - /anydesk
  - process.pe.product: AnyDesk
  - process.pe.description: AnyDesk
  - process.pe.company: AnyDesk Software GmbH
  - dns.question.name|endswith: .net.anydesk.com
  - destination.domain|endswith: .net.anydesk.com
  - user_agent.original|startswith: AnyDesk
  - network.application|startswith: AnyDesk
  - network.protocol|startswith: AnyDesk
  - action.properties.ServiceName: AnyDesk Service
  - registry.key|contains: \Services\AnyDesk
  - file.path|contains: \AppData\Roaming\AnyDesk\
  condition: selection'}

title: Cmd.exe Used To Run Reconnaissance Commands
rule:
{'uuid': 'e242b058-8efa-43bc-9741-b11aa1262262', 'name': 'Cmd.exe Used To Run Reconnaissance Commands', 'description': 'Detects command lines with suspicious args', 'severity': 20, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  parent_name:
    process.parent.name: cmd.exe
  cmdline:
  - process.command_line|re: (?i).*ipconfig\s+\/all.*
  - process.command_line|re: (?i).*arp\s+-a.*
  - process.command_line|re: (?i).*tasklist\s+-v.*
  - process.command_line|re: (?i).*sc\s+query.*
  condition: parent_name and cmdline'}

title: Powershell Winlogon Helper DLL
rule:
{'uuid': '1e1a9c05-7f55-48f6-ace9-20bc1cc58963', 'name': 'Powershell Winlogon Helper DLL', 'description': 'Detects modifications to the Winlogon Registry keys, which may cause Winlogon to load and execute malicious DLLs and/or executables.', 'severity': 40, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  action:
    event.code: 4104
    action.properties.ScriptBlockText|contains:
    - Set-ItemProperty
    - New-Item
  winlogon:
    action.properties.ScriptBlockText|contains:
    - CurrentVersion\\Winlogon
  event_registry:
  - registry.key|endswith:
    - SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Shell
    - SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Notify
    - SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Userinit
  - registry.path|endswith:
    - SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Shell
    - SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Notify
    - SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Userinit
  condition: (action and winlogon) or event_registry'}

{'uuid': '1c6bd311-8f05-4188-bdbf-42d95b66536d', 'name': 'Opening Of a Password File', 'description': 'Command line detection of common office software opening some password related file. It could be a security breach if an unauthorized user access it.', 'severity': 30, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  file_name:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - mdp
    - password
    - mot de passe
    - mots de passe
  process:
    process.name:
    - notepad.exe
    - winword.exe
    - excel.exe
    - powerpnt.exe
    - outlook.exe
  filter1:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - firefox.exe
    - msedge.exe
    - chrome.exe
    - Office16
  filter2:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - reset
    - forgot
    - "R\xE9initialiser"
  condition: file_name and process and not (filter1 and filter2)'}

title: OneNote Suspicious Children Process
rule:
{'uuid': '51847f5e-3c0c-43b1-8d96-d52415efe4da', 'name': 'OneNote Suspicious Children Process', 'description': 'In January 2023, a peak of attacks using .one files was observed in the wild. This rule tries to detect the effect of such attempts using this technique.', 'severity': 50, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  process_name:
    process.parent.name: onenote.exe
  children_names:
    process.name|contains:
    - rundll32.exe
    - regsvr32.exe
    - bitsadmin.exe
    - certutil.exe
    - installutil.exe
    - schtasks.exe
    - wmic.exe
    - cscript.exe
    - wscript.exe
    - cmstp.exe
    - Microsoft.Workflow.Compiler.exe
    - regasm.exe
    - regsvcs.exe
    - mshta.exe
    - msxsl.exe
    - ieexec.exe
    - cmd.exe
    - powershell.exe
    - javaw.exe
    - pcalua.exe
    - curl.exe
    - scriptrunner.exe
    - certoc.exe
    - workfolders.exe
    - odbcconf.exe
    - msiexec.exe
    - msdt.exe
  children_explorer:
    process.name: explorer.exe
    process.command_line|contains:
    - .hta
    - .vb
    - .wsh
    - .js
    - .ps
    - .scr
    - .pif
    - .bat
    - .cmd
  children_susp_path:
    process.executable|contains:
    - \AppData\
    - \Users\Public\
    - \ProgramData\
    - \Windows\Tasks\
    - \Windows\Temp\
    - \Windows\System32\Tasks\
  lnk_file:
    file.path|contains|all:
    - \exported\
    - .lnk
    process.name: onenote.exe
  filter1:
    process.executable|contains|all:
    - \AppData\Local\Microsoft\OneDrive\
    - \FileCoAuth.exe
  filter2:
    process.executable|contains|all:
    - \AppData\Local\Microsoft\Teams\
    - \Teams.exe
  filter3:
    process.name: rundll32.exe
    process.command_line|contains: PrintHTML
  filter4:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - AppData\Local\Google\Chrome
    - AppData\Local\Mozilla
    - AppData\Local\BraveSoftware
    - AppData\Local\Vivaldi
    - AppData\Local\Programs\Opera
  condition: not 1 of filter* and ((process_name and 1 of children_*) or lnk_file)'}

title: MS Office Product Spawning Exe in User Dir
rule:
{'uuid': '991d16ff-8066-4abc-8caa-13a9ed3ea737', 'name': 'MS Office Product Spawning Exe in User Dir', 'description': 'Detects an executable in the users directory started from Microsoft Word, Excel, Powerpoint, Publisher or Visio. This is a common technique used by attackers with documents embedding macros. It requires Windows command line logging events.', 'severity': 70, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  selection:
    process.executable: c:\users*.exe
    process.parent.name|contains:
    - winword.exe
    - excel.exe
    - powerpnt.exe
    - mspub.exe
    - visio.exe
  filter:
    process.executable|endswith:
    - teams.exe
  filter2:
    process.executable|contains: appdata\local\microsoft\onedrive*filecoauth.exe
  filter3:
    process.name:
    - eikonboxnet.exe
    - eikon.exe
  condition: selection and not 1 of filter*'}

title: Suspicious Control Process
rule:
{'uuid': 'd70188f4-edf6-4017-86e8-5da3a10b05b4', 'name': 'Suspicious Control Process', 'description': 'Detects suspicious execution of control.exe process when used to execute a DLL file.', 'severity': 80, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  selection:
    process.name: control.exe
    process.command_line|contains:
    - .dll
    - .jpg
    - .png
    - .gif
    - .bmp
    - .jpeg
    - .TIFF
    - '.inf'
    - .dat
    - '.cpl:'
    - ../../..
    - /AppData/Local
    - ":Users\Public"
    - "AppData\Local"
  filter:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - input.dll
    - keymgr.dll
  condition: selection and not filter'}

title: Suspicious Windows Installer Execution
rule:
{'uuid': '20e7cc42-4d97-4307-8166-492381c6d1f0', 'name': 'Suspicious Windows Installer Execution', 'description': 'Detects suspicious execution of the Windows Installer service (msiexec.exe) which could be used to install a malicious MSI package hosted on a remote server.', 'severity': 50, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  selection1:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - msiexec

    - Remediated
  condition: selection'}

  process:
